item.title: Is it a bird? Is it a plane? No, it’s the first bisexual Superman
item.description: Superman fell for a reporter and now his son is doing the same, although this time the superhero's love interest is a man called Jay.

item.title: Climate change may already impact majority of humanity: study
item.description: The effects of climate change could already be impacting 85 percent of the world's population, an analysis of tens of thousands of scientific studies said Monday.

item.title: Burkina starts trial of alleged killers of left-wing idol Sankara
item.description: A military court in Ouagadougou on Monday began the long-awaited trial of 14 men, including the former president, accused in the assassination of Burkina Faso's left-wing leader Thomas SankaraÂ 34 years ago.

item.title: Trio win Nobel Economics Prize for ‘natural experiments’
item.description: Three US-based academics on Monday won the Nobel Economics Prize for research on the labour market using "natural experiments", or observational studies, that have revolutionised empirical research in the field, the jury said.

item.title: Merck seeks US authorization for Covid treatment pill
item.description: US pharmaceutical giant Merck on Monday applied for emergency use authorization of its oral anti-Covid drug in the United States, a major step towards finding a simple pill to treat the disease.

item.title: Czech politics in limbo as president in intensive care
item.description: Czech politics were thrown into uncertainty Monday with the president being treated by an elite team of intensive care specialists and his chief ally, billionaire Prime Minister Andrej Babis, defeated in a general election.
